HEADWORD: hipbone
<hw>hipbone</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>Either of two large flaring bones,
each forming one half of the <partof>pelvis</partof>; made up of the
<part>ilium</part> and <part>ischium</part> and
<part>pubis</part>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> innominate bone.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

